EINSTEIN GENERATIVE AI
Turn On Einstein Generative AI Data Collection and Storage

To collect Einstein generative AI audit and feedback data, turn it on in Einstein Setup.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Einstein generative AI is available in Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein generative AI is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions with an Einstein for Sales, Einstein for Platform, or Einstein for Service add-on. To purchase the Einstein for Sales, Einstein for Platform, or Einstein for Service add-on, contact your Salesforce account executive.

To turn on Einstein generative AI data collection and storage, ensure that Data Cloud is provisioned in your Salesforce org and that you’ve turned on Einstein.

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Einstein Feedback, and then select Einstein Feedback.
From the Einstein Feedback Setup page, turn on Collect and Store Einstein Generative AI Audit Data.

Einstein generative AI audit data and feedback data appear in Data Cloud within 24 hours after you turn on collection and storage.

You can turn off data collection and storage at any time using the toggle. When you turn off data collection and storage, the data stream collecting the data pauses. Any reports show a gap between the time you turn it off and turn it back on.
